Redshift and blueshift are terms that are used to describe the shift in the frequency or wavelength of light from an object. A redshift occurs when the frequency or wavelength of the light from an object decreases, and is typically associated with objects that are moving away from the observer. On the other hand, a blueshift occurs when the frequency or wavelength of the light from an object increases, and is typically associated with objects that are moving towards the observer. Redshift and blueshift are opposite phenomena, but they are not the same thing.


